/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:55:- The kill condition about omitted or renormalized forced modes is good, but it arrives late. The chain should require exact closure of the simulated system before Step 4, not discover dishonesty after interpreting trajectories.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:106:- exact closure bookkeeping,
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:124:The right way to view it is: if Chain 04 first freezes a stable, representation-invariant notion of near-closure, then Chain 03 can become a valuable stress test against that object. Without that gate, it mostly searches for a high score on its own surrogate. And even in the best case, a small exact survivor should be treated as serious anti-obstruction evidence, not an automatic clean kill of the firewall idea.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:7:The right repair is not to discard the chain. It is to narrow it into a downstream quantitative test that only starts after a stable near-closure object is fixed, uses one invariant dynamical observable, treats minimal packets as calibration rather than theorem scope, and allows an honest middle outcome where the leakage route itself fails to produce a class-uniform theorem.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:15:This is the load-bearing criticism. The original Step 1 acted as if one could simply choose a leakage functional and closure rule, but this mission already identified object-definition instability as a first-order risk. Also, exact Fourier support closure, helical triad bookkeeping, and conjugate completion are not interchangeable options on one level. The refined chain should therefore begin only after one stable near-closure object has been frozen, ideally by Chain 04.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:27:A closure ledger by itself is only kinematic data. To matter for the mission, the chain must lower-bound an observable that lives on a stated norm and time window relevant to Tao-like role dynamics. "Same normalization" is not enough. The refined chain must pick one invariant dynamical observable up front and reject any argument that only proves extra couplings exist.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:54:4. It allows three honest endings: a restricted-class positive lower bound, an explicit low-leakage family that preserves Tao-role logic over a stated window, or a precise obstruction showing why leakage-based arguments do not yield a presentable theorem.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:64:- The most plausible success mode is not a universal no-near-closure theorem, but either a restricted-class leakage bound or a clean diagnosis of why the leakage program cannot support such a theorem without stronger hypotheses.
