+# REPORT-SUMMARY
+
+- Goal:
+  promote a bounded family of exact candidate notions of `near-closed Tao
+  circuit` without drifting away from the Step-1 packet and canonicalization
+  freezes.
+
+- What was checked:
+  the Step-1 freeze outputs, Tao mechanism reconstruction, exact-NS
+  intervention map, the run-001 chain critique / repair stack, the
+  spectator-leakage planning chain, and the Step-2 receptionist search log.
+
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`
+
+- Promoted candidates:
+  `Template-Defect Near-Closure`
+  `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`
+  `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`
+
+- One key takeaway:
+  the best-supported Step-2 menu is exactly the bounded split hinted by the
+  local record:
+  one role-template notion,
+  one leakage-budget notion,
+  and one behavioral delayed-threshold notion.
+
+- Pro-near-circuit-friendly survivor:
+  `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`
+  survives honestly because it asks only for one exact finite activation
+  itinerary on a canonically frozen packet, not for Tao's literal averaged
+  coefficients.
+
+- Not promoted:
+  `projection-rigidity only`
+  was rejected because it names the enforcement mechanism behind the candidate
+  family, not a distinct near-closure object.
+
+- Main design rule:
+  every promoted candidate had to name one fixed packet class, one fixed
+  finite window, one threshold language, and one canonical sign / amplitude /
+  phase sheet.
